Predictive Power Comparison

Jingjing Tang

County Level Analysis

The difference between this analysis and the previous county level predictive power comparison is that, here we consider a larger geographic scope. The intersection of counties available for DV, FB CLI and FB CLI-in-community from 2020-05-06 to 2020-10-08 is considered. Counties with no data reported by GS indicators are assigned with a value 0.

Getting data

Prediction Preparation

Here we use code liberally borrowed from a blog post to perform a prediction task.

We can see that during some time periods, median scaled error for the cases + google-symptoms (anosmia, ageusia, A+A) model is more variable than other signals at county level and is at the same level as that of case-only model.

Calculating median scaled error over all dates and all counties available for DV, FB CLI and FB CLI-in-community for a given model, we see that adding symptoms as a predictor does not reduce th median scaled error much compared to a cases-only model.

“Are these differences in median scaled errors significant? It’s hard to say [for certain, given the spatial and temporal dependence of the data], but some basic hypothesis testing suggests that they probably are: below we conduct a sign test for whether the difference in the “Cases” model’s scaled error and each other model’s scaled error is centered at zero" (source).

Differences in model fit are (very) significantly different, ignoring dependence structure at the moment.

“To mitigate the dependence across time (which intuitively seems to matter more than that across space), we recomputed these tests in a stratified way, where for each day we run a sign test on the scaled errors between two models over all [geographic regions]. The results are plotted as histograms below”, where one count corresponds to one prediction date (source).

If the differences between models were not significant, we’d expect the distribution of p-values to be uniform. That is distinctly not what we see here. Model differences at both 7 and 14 days ahead have elevated (compared to expected) numbers of low p-values, suggesting significance.

We can see that models containing GS outperform the Cases only model and the Cases + GS A+ A model is as competitive as the Cases + DV signals. However, the GS related models do not outperform Cases + FB CLI and Cases + FB CLI-in-community models. Errors are calculated on a shared-time basis. With all models together, more dates are dropped and it causes shifts in some error values. In fact, compared with the results we got previously considering counties available for GS indicators only, it shows that the prediction of cases + GS model is of high quality in regions with data reported and is still valuable for a larger geographical scope.
